# whoop-analytics — AI context

The user is **Edward**. This is a personal data engineering project ingesting WHOOP
health data (recovery, sleep, strain, workouts) into BigQuery via Python + dbt.

## Before editing any file

1. Read `docs/cursor-workflow.md` (required).
2. Read `docs/mental-model.md` for the full pipeline picture.
3. Read the actual file(s) being edited before editing them.

## Stack

| Layer | Tool |
|-------|------|
| Source | WHOOP API v1 (OAuth 2.0) |
| Ingest | Python 3.13, scripts/fetch.py |
| Utils | utils/whoop_client.py (API), utils/bq_client.py (BigQuery) |
| Warehouse | BigQuery — raw: `whoop_raw`, dbt: `whoop_dbt` |
| Transform | dbt (BigQuery adapter) |
| Orchestration | GitHub Actions, cron 06:00 UTC |
| Quality | ruff, pytest, dbt tests |

## Hard rules

- Raw tables are append-only — never UPDATE/DELETE from `whoop_raw.*`
- All WHOOP API calls through `utils/whoop_client.py` (handles token refresh)
- All BigQuery calls through `utils/bq_client.py` (never inline client construction)
- No credentials in code — env vars only; see `.env.example` for the full list
- Python 3.13 only (`python3.13`, not `python3` which resolves to 3.14 on this Mac)
- BigQuery region always `us-central1` (not `US` multi-region)
- dbt staging models: rename + cast + dedup only; no business logic

## dbt conventions (mirrors ChessLytics)

- `stg_*` → view, one source table, no business logic
- `int_*` → view or table, joins + derivations
- `fct_*` → incremental merge, watermark on `loaded_at`
- `dim_*` → full table, slowly changing entities
- Dedup in staging with `QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY id ORDER BY uploaded_at DESC) = 1`
- Always `SAFE_DIVIDE` for rates; never raw division
- Always `not_null` + `unique` tests on primary keys

## After substantive changes

- Run `make lint` and `make test`
- Update Recent Changes in `docs/cursor-workflow.md`
- Append entry to `CHANGELOG.md`
- Update `docs/mental-model.md` if pipeline architecture changed

## Tone

No em dashes. No brochure language. Short commit messages with what/why/files.
